race.comment: GALILEO GOLD (5) came home strongly last start to finish second, beaten a nose at Strathalbyn. Peaking now and can get the job done. POWER DANCER (15) is lightly raced and should find this easier. Will likely drift back from his draw and be bursting through late. Big threat. FEAR THE ZOU (12) is another that should find this a bit easier, dropping back from a maiden in town. The form around her reads well and she gets in light. MIKKI TANGO (1) caught the eye first-up when rattling home into third. Strips fitter but is likely to get a long way back again from his wide draw. Watch for him launching late.
